<sect2 id="htmltaskreport_sorttasks"><title>sorttasks
&lt;criteria&gt;[, &lt; cirteria&gt;]</title>

<para><simplelist type=horiz columns=2>
<member>criteria:</member><member><link
linkend="sortingcriteria">SORTINGCRITERIA</link></member>
</simplelist></para>

<para>The sorting criteria specifies how the tasks in the generated report
will be sorted. If two items match a criteria they are sorted
according to the next criteria. Up to three criteria are supported.
Most sorting criterias come as pair of two, so the list can be sorted
in ascending order (suffix -up) or descending order (suffix -down).
Possible values are:</para>

<para><simplelist type=horiz columns=2>

<member><computeroutput>tree</computeroutput></member>
<member>This is the default and creates a list with subtasks
indented and grouped together. If this sorting is used, parent tasks
are shown when subtasks are not hidden, even if the parent task
matches the hide expression. <computeroutput>tree</computeroutput> can
only be used as the first criteria.</member>

<member><computeroutput>tree</computeroutput></member>
<member>Show nesting with indentation</member>

<member><computeroutput>indexup</computeroutput></member>
<member>Lowest index on top</member>

<member><computeroutput>indexdown</computeroutput></member>
<member>Highest index on top</member>

<member><computeroutput>idup</computeroutput></member>
<member>First <link linkend="id">ID</link> on top</member>

<member><computeroutput>iddown</computeroutput></member>
<member>Last <link linkend="id">ID</link> on top</member>

<member><computeroutput>fullnameup</computeroutput></member>
<member>First full name on top</member>

<member><computeroutput>fullnamedown</computeroutput></member>
<member>Last full name on top</member>

<member><computeroutput>nameup</computeroutput></member>
<member>First name on top</member>

<member><computeroutput>namedown</computeroutput></member>
<member>Last name on top</member>

<member><computeroutput>planstartup</computeroutput></member>
<member>Earliest plan start date on top. This has replaced the bogus
<computeroutput>startup</computeroutput></member>

<member><computeroutput>planstartdown</computeroutput></member>
<member>Latest plan start date on top. This has replaced the bogus
<computeroutput>startdown</computeroutput></member>

<member><computeroutput>planendup</computeroutput></member>
<member>Earliest plan end date on top. This has replaced the bogus
<computeroutput>endup</computeroutput></member>

<member><computeroutput>planenddown</computeroutput></member>
<member>Latest plan end date on top. This has replaced the bogus
<computeroutput>enddown</computeroutput></member>

<member><computeroutput>actualstartup</computeroutput></member>
<member>Ealiest actual start date on top</member>

<member><computeroutput>actualstartdown</computeroutput></member>
<member>Latest actual start date on top</member>

<member><computeroutput>actualendup</computeroutput></member>
<member>Ealiest actual end date on top</member>

<member><computeroutput>actualenddown</computeroutput></member>
<member>Latest actual end date on top</member>

<member><computeroutput>priorityup</computeroutput></member>
<member>Lowest priority on top</member>

<member><computeroutput>prioritydown</computeroutput></member>
<member>Highest priority on top</member>

<member><computeroutput>responsibleup</computeroutput></member>
<member>First name of responsible on top</member>

<member><computeroutput>responsibledown</computeroutput></member>
<member>Last name of responsible on top</member>

</simplelist></para>

</sect2>
